 Piacenza]]<br> {{flagicon|RUS}} [[VC Belogorie|Belogorie Belgorod]]<br> {{flagicon|UKR}} [[VC Lokomotyv Kharkiv]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Modena|Casa Modena]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Czarni Radom|Cerrad Czarni Radom]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]\n| medaltemplates   =\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{GER}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Championship]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|2014 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2017 Poland]]|}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[European Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold|[[2015 European Games|2015 Baku]]|[[Volleyball at the 2015 European Games \u2013 Men's tournament|Team]]}}\n}}\n'''Lukas Immanuel Kampa''' (born 29 November 1986) is a German [[volleyball]] player, a member of [[Germany men's national volleyball team]] and Polish club [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]], a bronze medalist of the [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Championship 2014]] and named Best Setter of the tournament.\n\n==Personal life==\nKampa was born in [[Bochum]], [[Germany]] as son of Ulrich Kampa - a former [[volleyball player]]. He has a sister and a brother David, who is also a [[volleyball player]].\n\n[[File:Lukas Kampa 2014-15 season.jpeg|thumb|Kampa as the [[Czarni Radom|Cerrad Czarni Radom]] player in season 2014/2015.]]\n\n==Career==\nFor the Germany national team, he had a very good tournament in the 2012 Olympic Qualification tournament. In 2012/13 he was part of a dynamic duo with Georg Grozer in Belgorod and became a Russian Cup winner. In 2014 he signed a contract with Polish club [[Czarni Radom|Cerrad Czarni Radom]].<ref>[http://www.echodnia.eu/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20140926/SPORT04/140929209 ''Lukas Kampa i Dirk Westphal do\u0142\u0105czyli do siatkarzy Cerrad Czarni Radom''] \u2013 echodnia.eu \u2013 26-09-2014</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Deutsche Volleyball-Bundesliga|German Championship]], with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2009/2010''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Deutsche Volleyball-Bundesliga|German Championship]], with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Russian Cup, with [[VC Belogorie|Belogorie Belgorod]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Russian Volleyball Super League|Russian Championship]], with [[VC Belogorie|Belogorie Belgorod]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Ukrainian Cup, with [[VC Lokomotyv Kharkiv]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Ukrainian Men's Volleyball Super League|Ukrainian Championship]], with [[VC Lokomotyv Kharkiv]]\n** '''2016/2017''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2016\u201317 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]\n** '''2018/2019''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2018\u201319 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2014''' [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]]\n** '''2015''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2015 European Games \u2013 Men's tournament|European Games]]\n** '''2017''' [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2014:''' [[2014 FIVB Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2015:''' [[German Volleyball Player of the Year]]\n* '''2020:''' [[Volleyball at the 2020 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's European qualification|European qualification for Summer Olympics]] \u2013 Best Setter\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links